 PART 1: APACHE KAFKA
================================================================================
  KAFKA CORE CONCEPTS (MENTAL MODEL)
  ------------------------------------

  Think of Kafka like a NEWSPAPER SYSTEM:
  - Publisher  = Newspaper company (writes stories)
  - Topic      = Newspaper category (Sports, Business, Tech)
  - Partition  = Physical printing press (parallel)
  - Offset     = Page number (your reading position)
  - Consumer   = Reader (reads at their own pace)
  - Group      = Office subscription (one copy shared among team)

  KAFKA ARCHITECTURE
  -------------------
                        KAFKA CLUSTER
  +----------------------------------------------------------+
  |                                                          |
  |   Topic: "order-events"                                  |
  |   +----------------------------------------------------+ |
  |   | Partition 0: [msg1][msg3][msg5][msg7]...           | |
  |   | Partition 1: [msg2][msg4][msg6][msg8]...           | |
  |   | Partition 2: [msg0][msg9][msg10][msg11]...         | |
  |   +----------------------------------------------------+ |
  |                                                          |
  |   Broker 1 (leader P0)   Broker 2 (leader P1,P2)        |
  |   Zookeeper / KRaft for coordination                     |
  +----------------------------------------------------------+
         ^                           |
         | produce                   | consume
         |                           v
  +--------------+         +-----------------------------+
  | Order Svc    |         | Consumer Group: payment-grp |
  | (Producer)   |         | Consumer A: reads P0        |
  |              |         | Consumer B: reads P1        |
  +--------------+         | Consumer C: reads P2        |
                           +-----------------------------+

  KEY RULES:
  - One partition is consumed by ONLY ONE consumer in a group
  - More partitions = more parallelism
  - Messages in a partition are ORDERED (offset sequence)
  - Consumer remembers where it left off (offset commit)
  - Multiple groups can read the SAME topic independently


  KAFKA MESSAGE FLOW (STEP BY STEP)
  -----------------------------------
  Producer                  Kafka Broker              Consumer
  --------                  ------------              --------
  create message
       |
       | send to topic "order-events"
       |-------------------------->
                             assign to partition
                             (by key hash or round-robin)
                             write to partition log
                             replicate to followers
                             ack back to producer
       |<--------------------------
  producer confirmed
                                           poll for messages
                                           <-----------------
                             send batch of messages
                             ------------------>
                                           process message
                                           commit offset
                                           <-----------------
                             offset stored (consumer position)


  KAFKA vs QUEUE (CRITICAL DIFFERENCE)
  --------------------------------------
  Traditional Queue:          Kafka Topic:
  +-----------------+         +---------------------------+
  | msg1            |         | offset: 0  1  2  3  4  5 |
  | msg2            |         | [m1][m2][m3][m4][m5][m6] |
  | msg3            |         |  ^              ^         |
  +-----------------+         | GroupA       GroupB       |
  msg consumed = DELETED       (reads independently)
                               msg stays for retention period
                               can replay from offset 0


