 PART 2: RABBITMQ
================================================================================
  RABBITMQ CORE CONCEPTS (MENTAL MODEL)
  ---------------------------------------
  Think of RabbitMQ like a POST OFFICE:
  - Producer   = Person sending a letter
  - Exchange   = Post office sorting room
  - Queue      = Post box / mailbox
  - Binding    = Routing rule (which mailbox gets which letter)
  - Consumer   = Person receiving mail
  - Routing Key= Address on envelope

  RABBITMQ EXCHANGE TYPES
  ------------------------
  1. DIRECT EXCHANGE (exact match routing)
     ---------------------------------------
     Producer sends with routingKey="payment"
     Exchange routes to queue bound with key="payment"

     Producer --> [Exchange] --(key=payment)--> [payment-queue] --> Consumer

  2. FANOUT EXCHANGE (broadcast to all queues)
     --------------------------------------------
     All bound queues get a copy regardless of routing key

     Producer --> [Exchange] --> [email-queue]     --> Email Consumer
                            --> [sms-queue]       --> SMS Consumer
                            --> [audit-queue]     --> Audit Consumer

  3. TOPIC EXCHANGE (wildcard routing)
     -------------------------------------
     Routing key: "order.placed.chennai"
     # = match zero or more words
     * = match exactly one word

     "order.#"         --> matches order.placed, order.placed.chennai
     "order.*.chennai" --> matches order.placed.chennai
     "#"               --> matches everything

  4. HEADERS EXCHANGE (match on message headers)
     -----------------------------------------------
     Route by header values instead of routing key


  RABBITMQ ARCHITECTURE FLOW
  ---------------------------
  Producer
     |
     | publish(exchange="order-exchange", routingKey="order.placed")
     v
  +-----------------+
  |    Exchange     |  (applies routing rules)
  | order-exchange  |
  | type: topic     |
  +-+---+---+-------+
    |   |   |
    |   |   +-- routingKey "order.#"    --> [order-queue]     --> Payment Svc
    |   |
    |   +------ routingKey "#"          --> [audit-queue]     --> Audit Svc
    |
    +---------- routingKey "order.placed" --> [email-queue]   --> Email Svc

  Queue stores message until consumer picks it up.
  Message DELETED from queue after consumer ACKs.


  DEAD LETTER QUEUE (DLQ) FLOW
  ------------------------------
  Consumer fails to process
         |
         | NACK (negative acknowledgement)
         v
  [order-queue] -- x-dead-letter-exchange --> [order-dlq]
                                                    |
                                              Dead Letter Consumer
                                              (alert, log, manual fix)


