 PART 3: AZURE SERVICE BUS
================================================================================
  AZURE SERVICE BUS CORE CONCEPTS
  ---------------------------------

  Think of Azure Service Bus like a MANAGED COURIER SERVICE:
  - Namespace  = Courier company (top-level container)
  - Queue      = Package drop-off (one receiver picks it up)
  - Topic      = Broadcast channel (multiple subscribers get copy)
  - Subscription = Subscriber's personal mailbox with filter
  - Session    = Labeled batch (guarantees ordering per label)

  QUEUE vs TOPIC IN SERVICE BUS
  ------------------------------
  Queue (point-to-point):
  Sender --> [Queue] --> ONE receiver (competing consumers)

  Topic (pub/sub):
  Sender --> [Topic] --> [Sub A: filter="status=NEW"] --> Consumer A
                     --> [Sub B: filter="amount>1000"] --> Consumer B
                     --> [Sub C: no filter]            --> Consumer C


  AZURE SERVICE BUS ARCHITECTURE
  --------------------------------
  +------------------------------------------------------+
  |  Azure Service Bus Namespace                         |
  |  (servicebus.windows.net)                            |
  |                                                      |
  |  Queue: order-queue                                  |
  |  +--------------------------------------------------+|
  |  | [msg1: lock 30s][msg2: lock 30s][msg3]...        ||
  |  |  ^-- consumer locks msg, processes, then deletes ||
  |  |  If not completed in 30s --> lock released       ||
  |  +--------------------------------------------------+|
  |                                                      |
  |  Topic: order-events                                 |
  |  +--------------------------------------------------+|
  |  |                                                  ||
  |  |  Subscription: payment-sub (filter: all)         ||
  |  |  Subscription: vip-sub (filter: amount > 10000)  ||
  |  |  Subscription: audit-sub (filter: all)           ||
  |  +--------------------------------------------------+|
  |                                                      |
  |  Dead Letter Queue (auto-created per queue/sub)      |
  |  Max delivery count: 10 (configurable)               |
  +------------------------------------------------------+


  SERVICE BUS vs KAFKA vs RABBITMQ
  ----------------------------------
  Feature             Kafka           RabbitMQ        Azure Svc Bus
  ------------------- --------------- --------------- ---------------
  Type                Log/Stream      Queue/Exchange  Queue/Topic
  Managed             Self/Confluent  Self/CloudAMQP  Fully managed
  Throughput          Very High       High            Medium-High
  Message replay      Yes             No              No
  Ordering            Per partition   No (mostly)     Per session
  Dead letter         Manual (DLT)    Manual (DLQ)    Auto built-in
  Message size        Default 1MB     128MB           256KB/100MB
  Best for            Event streaming Task queues     Enterprise Azure
  Protocol            Kafka protocol  AMQP            AMQP / JMS 2.0
  Cost                Infra cost      Infra cost      Pay per message


