 PART 4: SPRING CLOUD STREAM (UNIFIED ABSTRACTION)
================================================================================
  WHAT IS SPRING CLOUD STREAM?
  ------------------------------
  Spring Cloud Stream is an abstraction layer that lets you write
  messaging code ONCE and switch between Kafka, RabbitMQ, or
  Azure Service Bus by changing only the binder dependency.

  Your Code                Binder              Broker
  ---------                ------              ------
  @Bean Function  ------>  Kafka Binder  ----> Apache Kafka
  @Bean Function  ------>  Rabbit Binder ----> RabbitMQ
  @Bean Function  ------>  Azure Binder  ----> Azure Service Bus


  SPRING CLOUD STREAM ARCHITECTURE
  ----------------------------------
  +--------------------------------------------------------------+
  |  Spring Boot Application                                     |
  |                                                              |
  |  +------------------+      +---------------------------+    |
  |  |  Source          |      |  Sink                     |    |
  |  |  (Producer)      |      |  (Consumer)               |    |
  |  |  @Bean Supplier  |      |  @Bean Consumer           |    |
  |  +--------+---------+      +------------+--------------+    |
  |           |                             |                    |
  |  +--------v-----------------------------v--------------+    |
  |  |         Spring Cloud Stream Binder Layer             |    |
  |  |   (Handles serialization, error, retry, DLQ)         |    |
  |  +------------------------------------------------------+    |
  +--------------------------------------------------------------+
                    |                      |
                    v                      ^
             Message Broker (Kafka / RabbitMQ / Azure)


  DEPENDENCY (switch binder to change broker):
  --------------------------------------------
  <!-- For Kafka -->
  <dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.cloud</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka</artifactId>
  </dependency>

  <!-- For RabbitMQ -->
  <dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.cloud</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-cloud-stream-binder-rabbit</artifactId>
  </dependency>

  <!-- For Azure Service Bus -->
  <dependency>
    <groupId>com.azure.spring</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-cloud-azure-stream-binder-servicebus</artifactId>
  </dependency>


  FUNCTIONAL PROGRAMMING MODEL:
  ------------------------------
  @Configuration
  public class OrderStreamFunctions {

      // Supplier = produces messages on schedule
      @Bean
      public Supplier<OrderEvent> orderSupplier() {
          return () -> orderService.getNextPendingOrder();
      }

      // Consumer = receives messages
      @Bean
      public Consumer<OrderEvent> processPayment() {
          return event -> paymentService.process(event);
      }

      // Function = receive, transform, and forward
      @Bean
      public Function<OrderEvent, PaymentEvent> orderToPayment() {
          return order -> new PaymentEvent(order.getId(), order.getAmount());
      }
  }

